Bing

Senior Software Engineer
What if your job description were simply make tomorrow better?   That’s the essence of roles within our Bing Team. Every day, we bring an insatiable curiosity to the table, challenging ourselves to reimagine what is and what can be.   We build on what’s come before to create what’s next. 

The Bing Monetization team needs a software developer with exceptional breadth, depth, and creativity. Join a team with a responsibility to experiment quickly, with experiments leads to shipping code that is truly on the cutting edge of large scale data mining, search and user engagement.
We are looking for developers who are masters at rendering grids, images, text on all devices and browsers.   Developers who can dance through the minefields of semantic markup, to client script rendering frameworks and all of the warts and performance issues in between.   Developers who can see how the page renders and anticipate how users will engage in the final product. If you’re serious about developing advanced web user experiences, working across technologies – Windows, Edge, Phone, iOS, Android - to not just use them but help define them, and pleasing millions of customers along the way, this is the most exciting place you can be right now.

Our team is responsible for the layout, rendering, and optimization of ads across all Bing properties while balancing revenue with user and site grow.   Our team delivers some of the highest revenue gains per developer anywhere at Microsoft. In addition to refining the core ads user experience, we develop new advertising features, and apply data-driven optimization techniques to maximize revenue without sacrificing the quality of the overall search experience. We work with interpreting hundreds of machine learning features, creating and testing machine learning models, and supporting infrastructure to place the items on the page. 

The Bing team ships on a daily basis, from a single source tree shared by hundreds of engineers across multiple continents. In order to ensure that we have the best user experience possible, we run thousands of cloud-based test cases for every single check-in, reusing a number of open-source tools and techniques. We don’t have the concept of “test passes” or “test environments” - our test pass begins at check-in time, everything has the same priority, we validate experiences at scale and in production. 

Required Qualifications: 
• 5+ years demonstrated experience in designing and developing enterprise-level internet scale services/solutions. 
• Solid design and programming skills in C# or Java. 
• Solid hands-on software development expertise including object oriented design skills, .NET etc. 
• Demonstrated ability to impact/influence engineering designs 
• Development experience using full stack web client technologies on large-scale applications 
• Solid technical aptitude and problem solving skills 
• Strong debugging skills 

Desired Qualifications: 
• Experience with web analytics, metrics, and how to measure successful engagement on web sites.
• Experience in UX Design, graphics and user interaction on web pages. 
• Understanding and experience in Machine Learning a plus. 
• Experience with Big Data/Analytic Systems like Cosmos or Hadoop implementations 

Education Qualification: 
• Master or Bachelor degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or equivalent with related engineering experience is required.


Our team is responsible for the layout, rendering, and optimization of ads across all Bing properties while balancing revenue with user and site grow.   Our team delivers some of the highest revenue and user value gains per developer anywhere at Microsoft. In addition to refining the core ads user experience, we develop new advertising features, and apply data-driven optimization techniques to maximize revenue without sacrificing the quality of the overall search experience. We have a long road ahead and we need your help! Key to our continued success in this hypercompetitive space is taking enormous volumes of data and turning them into useful, actionable information to drive increased user engagement through great Bing features and improvements.

